HELMOPS Rebirth — Roadmap

 Context

 HELM today is a half-built ReAct chat agent wearing a monitoring TUI as a hat. Senior DevOps will not adopt it as a daily driver because:

 1. The dashboard fails the 5-second test. 10 tabs, 3-line status bar, truncated metadata, no severity grouping, no trend lines. The eye has no anchor.
 2. Selection jumps on live refresh. selected_finding: usize (tui.rs:1143) is a positional index; refresh_dashboard (tui.rs:4808) rebuilds the findings Vec wholesale. The clamp at L4351
 only fires on filter/sort, not refresh. The operator literally cannot read a finding before it switches under them.
 3. WHY pane is duplicate spam. tui.rs:6066 iterates correlated_finding_ids with zero dedup, emitting "● WARN has failed..." ~20× in a row.
 4. Scope is single-host. No fleet view. RemoteRegistry exists but the dashboard never iterates it. No Kubernetes, no libvirt/QEMU, no Docker Compose collectors.
 5. No alerting. Findings sit in a TUI; pager never fires.
 6. Auto-plan generation absent. Operators must Alt+G manually per finding, then wait. No background cache, no fingerprint-keyed memoization.
 7. Massive dead surface. 31 top-level CLI commands, 4 TUI modes (Chat/Plan/Diagnose/Auto), agent JSON-RPC server, MCP, skills, episodes, sessions, replay — all noise for a sysadmin who
 just wants helm watch.

 Outcome. Rebirth as HELMOPS: a TUI-first incident-and-monitoring daily driver. Operator opens it, sees the top problem in ≤5 seconds, reads a fix plan auto-generated in the background,
 applies it with one keystroke, and the audit log proves what happened. Strip the agent. Keep the security spine (capability gate, taint, HMAC audit). Add fleet, K8s, libvirt, Compose, real
  alerting.

 ---
 Strip / Keep / Add (Ruthless)

 STRIP (delete entire files / modules)

 - helm-cli/src/serve.rs — agent JSON-RPC server.
 - helm-cli/src/agent_remote.rs, hooks.rs, ndjson_sink.rs, snapshot_sink.rs — agent event sinks.
 - crates/helm-agent/ — the ReAct loop crate (entire crate).
 - TuiMode::Chat | Plan | Diagnose | Auto (main.rs:275) and their routing (main.rs:1721). Keep only Dashboard.
 - CLI commands: episodes, skills, sessions, mcp, replay, memory, profile, undo, redo, export, stats, serve, chat, plan, diagnose, auto.
 - Agent-only tools from crates/helm-tools/: anything not used by helm-monitor/src/execute.rs apply-plan path.
 - TUI tabs: collapse 10 → 5 (kill Assist, fold Processes+Network+Storage into Resources, keep Alerts, Services, Resources, Logs, Changes).
 - WHY-pane raw-correlation iteration (tui.rs:6060-6091).

 KEEP (security + signal spine)

 - 16 detectors + 14 collectors (crates/helm-monitor/).
 - HMAC-chained audit log (append-only, verifies after every episode).
 - Tainted<T> propagation and TaintLevel::External on browser/SSH/MCP inputs.
 - Capability gate before every tool call. *.write blocked on tainted input.
 - Finding lifecycle (open/new/recurring/suppressed/resolved/self-resolved) + stable fingerprint (findings.rs:224).
 - Changesets (config-diff snapshots).
 - Multi-provider LLM (anthropic, gemini, ollama, openai_compat, mock) — for narrative/plan generation only.
 - RemoteRegistry (extend, don't replace).
 - Apply-plan path (crates/helm-monitor/src/execute.rs) — independent of agent, safe.
 - host_hostname-keyed snapshot store (crates/helm-memory/src/snapshots.rs).
 - Secrets policy: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/helm/secrets.toml mode 0600; no env auto-import.

 ADD

 - Sparkline history per metric (cpu/mem/disk/net/loadavg) — ring buffer in DashboardData.
 - Severity-grouped finding list (CRIT / WARN / INFO) with fingerprint-stable selection.
 - Fleet panel: parallel SSH JoinSet, host_id UUID, credential abstraction.
 - K8s collector via kubectl wrapper (events, pod status, restarts, OOMKills).
 - libvirt/QEMU collector via virsh wrapper (domain state, snapshots, host load).
 - Docker Compose collector (project-level, layered over existing Docker collector).
 - Alerting sinks: webhook, Slack, PagerDuty — gated by severity + dedup window.
 - Auto-plan generation: on finding selection, spawn background LLM call, cache by fingerprint, render when ready, no blocking.
 - Configurable thresholds via $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/helm/thresholds.toml.
 - helm watch as default subcommand (zero-arg launch goes straight to dashboard).

