 Roadmap

 Every task = atomic commit gated by cargo fmt --check && cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo test --workspace --all-targets. Each slice ends with a verification
 gate. Each milestone ends with the deterministic RC gate (cargo test deterministic_100_run -- --ignored).

 M1 — UX Foundation + Agent Strip (the rebirth)

 Goal: Operator opens HELMOPS, sees grouped findings, selects one, reads it without it jumping, and the binary is half the size.

 - Slice 1.1 — Fix selection-jump bug.
   - T1.1.1: Replace selected_finding: usize with selected_fingerprint: Option<u64>. Capture fingerprint pre-refresh in refresh_dashboard (tui.rs:4808), restore index post-refresh by
 fingerprint lookup, fall back to clamp.
   - T1.1.2: Add unit test: build findings Vec [A,B,C], select B, replace Vec with [A,C,B,D], assert selection still on B.
   - Verify: test passes; manual helm watch for 30s confirms selection sticky across refreshes.
   - Deliverable: commit fix(tui): pin finding selection by fingerprint across live refresh.
 - Slice 1.2 — Fix WHY-pane dedup.
   - T1.2.1: At tui.rs:6060-6091, group correlated findings by title via HashMap<String, (Severity, usize)>, render ● {sev} {title} (×{count}).
   - T1.2.2: Snapshot test on a synthetic finding with 17 correlations → expect 1 line (×17).
   - Verify: snapshot test; manual inspection on the nginx-5xx scenario.
   - Deliverable: commit fix(tui): collapse duplicate correlations in WHY pane.
 - Slice 1.3 — Tab + status-bar collapse.
   - T1.3.1: Reduce OpsTab enum (tui.rs:852-865) to 5 variants: Alerts, Services, Resources, Logs, Changes. Move Processes/Network/Storage render fns under Resources tab via sub-section
 toggle.
   - T1.3.2: Compress status bar to single line (host, fleet count, uptime, clock, tab list, hotkeys).
   - T1.3.3: Severity-group left pane: CRIT block, WARN block, INFO block, with sparklines beneath.
   - Verify: snapshot test of dashboard render at 120×40; cargo run -- watch visual diff against mockup.
   - Deliverable: commit feat(tui): collapse to 5 tabs + severity-grouped left pane.
 - Slice 1.4 — Strip the agent.
   - T1.4.1: Delete helm-cli/src/{serve,agent_remote,hooks,ndjson_sink,snapshot_sink}.rs + their mod lines in main.rs. Delete crates/helm-agent. Remove from workspace Cargo.toml.
   - T1.4.2: Remove TuiMode::{Chat,Plan,Diagnose,Auto} variants + routing (main.rs:275-282, 1721-1725). Default subcommand → watch.
   - T1.4.3: Delete CLI commands listed in STRIP section from Commands enum (main.rs:133-187). Update help text.
   - T1.4.4: Run cargo build, fix orphaned helm_agent:: imports at L35, L5902, L6458, L6462, L7030.
   - T1.4.5: Validate apply-plan still works (execute.rs:235-293 uses std::process::Command directly, no agent dep). Add integration test invoking apply_plan on a 2-step plan.
   - Verify: full workspace builds clean; binary size compared pre/post (expect ≥30% drop); apply-plan integration test green.
   - Deliverable: commit refactor: strip ReAct agent + chat/plan/diagnose modes; helm watch is the product.

 M1 gate: cargo fmt --check, cargo clippy -- -D warnings, full workspace test suite, deterministic_100_run.

 ---
 M2 — Real-Time Trends

 Goal: Operator sees the curve, not just the current value.

 - Slice 2.1 — Ring-buffer history in DashboardData. Add VecDeque<f64> per metric (cpu/mem/disk/net/load), cap 60 points, push on each refresh.
 - Slice 2.2 — Ratatui Sparkline rendering beneath severity groups (left pane bottom strip).
 - Slice 2.3 — Per-tab sparklines: Resources tab gets large sparklines for top-N processes/disks/interfaces.
 - Slice 2.4 — Configurable refresh cadence + history depth via thresholds.toml.

 M2 gate: render perf budget — full dashboard refresh ≤16ms at 60 findings + 5 sparklines. Benchmark in cargo bench.

 ---
 M3 — Fleet (Multi-Host)

 Goal: One dashboard, N hosts, parallel.

 - Slice 3.1 — Extend RemoteEntry (remote.rs:28) with host_id: Uuid; migrate registry file.
 - Slice 3.2 — Parallel SSH JoinSet in RemoteRegistry; collect findings from N hosts concurrently. Benchmark at N=20.
 - Slice 3.3 — Credential abstraction: enum Credential { SshAgent, KeyFile(PathBuf), Password(Secret) }. No password in registry file.
 - Slice 3.4 — Fleet panel in TUI: header shows fleet: 12/12 up; new tab [6]Fleet (re-add as 6th tab — fleet view warrants it). Per-host CRIT counts.

 M3 gate: 20-host fixture (mock SSH responder) completes full refresh in ≤2s; HMAC chain verifies across multi-host episode.

 ---
 M4 — Kubernetes / VM / Compose

 Goal: Cover the real infrastructure surface.

 - Slice 4.1 — Kubernetes collector via kubectl wrapper (crates/helm-monitor/src/collectors/kubernetes.rs): events (Warning), pod restarts, OOMKills, PVC pressure. Capability-gated
 KubectlRead.
 - Slice 4.2 — libvirt/QEMU collector via virsh wrapper: domain state, snapshot age, host load.
 - Slice 4.3 — Docker Compose collector: layered over existing Docker collector, groups containers by project label.
 - Slice 4.4 — Detector tuning for new finding types; thresholds in thresholds.toml.

 M4 gate: integration tests against a kind cluster + a libvirt test VM + a compose fixture, all in CI matrix.

 ---
 M5 — Alerting

 Goal: It pages people.

 - Slice 5.1 — Alert routing module (crates/helm-monitor/src/alerting/mod.rs): severity threshold, dedup window per fingerprint, rate limit.
 - Slice 5.2 — Webhook sink (HTTP POST, JSON body, retry with backoff).
 - Slice 5.3 — Slack sink (incoming webhook URL, channel override, severity color).
 - Slice 5.4 — PagerDuty sink (Events API v2, dedup_key = finding fingerprint).

 M5 gate: end-to-end: trigger CRIT finding in mock → PD event fires within 5s → resolution event fires on lifecycle close.

 ---
 M6 — AI Excellence

 Goal: Operator selects a finding; a fix plan is already waiting.

 - Slice 6.1 — Auto-plan generation on selection: on selected_fingerprint change, spawn background tokio::task that calls LLM; cache result by fingerprint in Arc<DashMap<Fingerprint,
 PlanState>>.
 - Slice 6.2 — Render cached plan in FIX PLAN section instantly if cache hit; "generating…" spinner otherwise.
 - Slice 6.3 — Plan-quality test: golden fixtures of 20 findings × 5 providers, snapshot test for structure (numbered steps, capability-gated commands, no destructive ops without confirm).
 - Slice 6.4 — [a]apply hotkey wires to execute.rs apply-plan path with capability gate + taint check + audit append.

 M6 gate: cache hit ratio ≥80% on second open of same finding; deterministic_100_run still green; HMAC chain verifies across apply episode.

